			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">After I hit level 44, I went to Rathe Mountains to try the HGs there. The competition was so thich that I gave up post-haste.<br><br>I then went to Velious. Did a bit of my coldain prayer shawl quests and headed to easter wastes. Suffice to say the stuff there was so nasty they chewed through my fire pet in seconds. I left again<br><br>I then thought I'd give the seafuries a go. I'd heard so many great things about them... But I thought I'd be overmatched again...<br><br>Well boy was I wrong! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="icon_biggrin" border="0" /> --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT="<img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="icon_biggrin" border="0" />"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>I buff myself with<br>Arch Shielding (duh!)<br>Phantom Plate (hp regen)<br>Levitate (ability to med while over the sea)<br><br>I summoned my Focused Level 44 Fire pet. (200m)<br>Decked it out with...<br>2 Summon: Daggers (20m)<br>2 Summon: Coldstones (80m)<br>2 Summon: Rings of Flight (200m)<br>1 Summon: Elemental Defender (40m)<br>1 Summon: Phantom Plate (300m)<br><br>That's 840 manna on one pet. Not too bad.<br><br>I then wait for FireElementalAura to be cast (within 2 minutes it's on), buffed with Burnout 2 (negligable difference. Forgot to reapply many times) and /pet guard here on the shoreline.<br><br>I went to pull any seafury (making sure to leave Tainted, Corrputed and Quag well alone!) with Fire Bolt (lvl 8 spell) if ti was far away or Malisement if I was feeling adventurous.<br><br>I dragged the thing back to the shore to my pet and depending on whether I pulled with Fire Bolt or Malisement, I either did or did not (respectively) have time to turn, judge distance and do /pet attack. I coudl with Fire Bolt but with Malisement, I settled for counting to 5 after approaching pet then hitting /pet attack)<br><br>Once the pet has engaged the seafury, I wait for the first &quot;Tauntign attacker, Master&quot; before I medidate or I'll most likely have the big one-eyed freak chasing me.<br><br>I monitor the pet and seafury's health and usually throw a nuke after the second or third &quot;Taunting Attacker Master&quot; message. Now here's where I get a little crazy...<br><br>Before or after my first nuke, I step into melee range. I take a few hits from the seafury (usually 1 - 1 1/2 bubbles worth of HP) and then back off. I gain some defence skill (144 right now! RAH!) and buy my pet a little time.<br><br>I then steadily nuke keeping the seafury's HPs along the same level as my pet's. I double tap the sit/stand button (so I sit for a split second then stand again) to see if the seafury moves a bit. If it does, I dont' re-nuke straight away, if it doesn't, then I fire off another Shock of Swords. I repeat until the seafury is at 1 1/2 bubbles of HP. one more SoS si enough to reduce him to 1/2 a red of HP. If not, then I follow up with a lesser nuke (Blaze or Shock of Spikes). Usually the Seafury is still hitting the pet due to its low HPs. Noe we exploit the pet aggro &quot;nerf&quot; that verant did where pets cannot hold aggro when another PC is within melee range.<br><br>You will be at roughly 80% health. Once you step into melee range, the seafury will switch to you, see your high health %age and begin to flee. Stay within melee range while your pet finishes it off and neither of you will be hit.<br><br>This method should only use 40% of your manna pool, but if something bad happens (partial resists or your pet takes a beating) I reccomend onyl engaging a Seafury if your manna is 70%. As you gain levels, you can play more risky games... At level 48, I can take them down with onyl 40% manna, but any less than that and I'm asking for trouble!<br><br>In the end the onyl spells you really need to cast are...<br>1 Malismenet (100m) rarely resisted in my experience<br>4 Shock fo Swords (250m, 1000 total)<br><br>Hope this helps you all and if you're on AB, don't you dare train me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Majishia Vie <Wyrd Angles>Magician of the 47th Bummed SummoningAntonius Bayle</p><i></i></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
