				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Ok, I have talked with a 61 mage asking about certain items I have read here that people give their pets and really want to know the reason for each one ( well, the ones I can't see a justiification for ).
<br />

<br />
2 Summon: Daggers (20m) - for dual wield, makes sense.
<br />
2 Summon: Coldstones (80m) - no clue, unless it is nightlight, why give a    
<br />
   coldstone to your pet? And why 2 of them?
<br />
2 Summon: Rings of Flight (200m) - no clue, what does pet use 2 rings of 
<br />
 flight for?  
<br />
1 Summon: Elemental Defender (40m) - defense, goes in range slot or back slot ( I assume pet can only have one since it is lore, I have read in these forums of people giving them 2, one for each slot. But that doesn't make sense since it is lore. ). 
<br />
1 Summon: Phantom Plate (300m) - defensive, make perfect sense. 
<br />

<br />
One note is I tried giving my fire pet focus items to see if his casting / damage improve but I really haven't seen a difference one way of the other. 
<br />

<br />
If you could explain the items I noted I have no clue about ( the justification ), I would appreciate it as I am actuall the highest level mage in my guild and everyone asks me questions.<br />_________________<br />Dyyre Straights 
<br />
Evil Mage on Bertoxxulus</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
