Not just any daggers, but the Daggers of Symbol. It's usually used to up pet resists, and if the pet is not the 44 summon, activate dual-wielding.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">2 Summon: Coldstones (80m) - no clue, unless it is nightlight, why give a coldstone to your pet? And why 2 of them?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
For the AC on the necklace. One for the neck slot, and one of the ammo slot. The focus item can be substituted for the neck slot, since that also adds a little bit of hp, instead of just AC.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">2 Summon: Rings of Flight (200m) - no clue, what does pet use 2 rings of flight for? </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
