<br />
Pets dual wield without weapons at 34 now that we summon max level pets.  
<br />

<br />
The reason you see mages giving their pets weapons after 34 is to allow the use of an elemental defender in the back slot of the pet... more AC for the pet.  If you don't give the pet two weapons first, then the pet will equip it as a shield, and that will reduce its DPS.
<br />

<br />
And, of course, proc'ing weapons allow the pet to fight better.  Sword of Runes against summoned creatures, Blade of Walnan and its ilk against most everything.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">2 Summon: Coldstones (80m) - no clue, unless it is nightlight, why give a coldstone to your pet? And why 2 of them?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
For the AC on the necklace. One for the neck slot, and one of the ammo slot. The focus item can be substituted for the neck slot, since that also adds a little bit of hp, instead of just AC.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
You don't get AC from the ammo slot.  In fact, you get no bonuses whatsoever from the ammo slot... only ultravision.  There's no reason to summon two of them.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">1 Summon: Elemental Defender (40m) - defense, goes in range slot or back slot ( I assume pet can only have one since it is lore, I have read in these forums of people giving them 2, one for each slot. But that doesn't make sense since it is lore. ). </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
