				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I wrote that FAQ pre my usage of focus items, also I had a 2 hr connection timeout via a modem so investing X-manna in a pet became fruitless.
<br />

<br />
The Coldstones were provided twice since I have no way of knowing which slot the pet put it in. If they default put it in the ammo slot, then the pet gains nothing from it. Providing it with two assures me that one goes in the neck slot.
<br />

<br />
The same goes for the summoned rings of flight for their AC pre my discovery of Naki's rings.
<br />

<br />
Since the introductions of pet armour and focus items, I ammend my post to include...
<br />

<br />
2 Daggers (20 manna) (to assure that the ED goes in the back slot)
<br />
Elemental Defender (40 manna)
<br />
Phantom Plate (300 manna)
<br />
Golden Choker (120 manna)
<br />
Silk Mantle (120 manna)
<br />
Jolum's Bauble (120 manna)
<br />
Twisted Ring (120 manna)
<br />
Ruby Bracelet (120 manna)
<br />

<br />
Total: 960 manna (+200 for pet = 1160)
<br />

<br />
There has been evidence to suggest that pets only equip one bracer, applying the same logic to earrings and rings, there's little point in providing them as well.
<br />

<br />
Of course, later in the life of a Mage, investing in a pet becomes partly fruitless.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=320122" target="_blank" class="postlink">Majishia Vie </a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=827513" target="_blank" class="postlink">Fayth Vanquisher </a>
<br />
Wyrd Angles
<br />
Antonius Bayle
<br />

<br />
